      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:5:24:6",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) مَمْلُوكٌ فِي يَدِهِ مَالٌ أَ عَلَيْهِ زَكَاةٌ قَالَ لَا قُلْتُ وَ لَا عَلَى سَيِّدِهِ قَالَ لَا إِنَّهُ لَمْ يَصِلْ إِلَى سَيِّدِهِ وَ لَيْسَ هُوَ لِلْمَمْلُوكِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, form Muhammad Bin Ahmad, from Al Khasshab, from Ali Bin Al Husayn, from Muhammad Bin Abu Hamza, from Abdullah Bin Sinan who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘An owned slave has wealth in his hands, would there be <span class=\"iTxt\">Zakāt</span> upon him?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘No’. I said, ‘Nor upon his master?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘No. It is what he did not give to his master, and it is not for the owned slave’."
        ]
      }
    }
